    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-09-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-09-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="290" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d290">
                <head>No. 290.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Maury</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-09-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 14,
                            1888</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 100.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 136, of the 9th
                        ultimo, in which you refer to the political condition of Colombia, and to
                        the disapproval shown as regards President Nuñez’ offensive reference to
                        foreign Governments, inclosing at the same time the inaugural speech of Dr.
                        Holguin on his assuming the Presidential office.</p>
                <p>Your dispatch has been read with much satisfaction.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F.
                            Bayard.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
